source: crates/gaussclaw-conformance/src/cli_parity.rs
expression: render_help()
---
GaussClaw — Hermes-compatible agent on the Gauss-Aether runtime.

Usage: gaussclaw [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  chat     One-shot chat REPL without launching the full TUI (GaussClaw extension)
  model    Select or inspect the active LLM model. (Hermes parity: `hermes model`.)
  tools    Enable, disable, or list tools. (Hermes parity: `hermes tools`.)
  config   Read or write configuration values. (Hermes parity: `hermes config`.)
  gateway  Start, stop, or inspect the messaging gateway. (Hermes parity: `hermes gateway`.)
  setup    Interactive first-run setup wizard. (Hermes parity: `hermes setup`.)
  update   Update GaussClaw to the latest signed release. (Hermes parity: `hermes update`.)
  doctor   Run the Self-Diagnostic Health Engine invariants. (Hermes parity: `hermes doctor`.)
  import   Import a Hermes config and migrate it to GaussClaw (GaussClaw extension)
  receipt  Inspect the receipt chain head or verify an envelope (GaussClaw extension)
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -c, --config <PATH>  Path to an alternate `gaussclaw.toml`. If omitted, the loader walks the
                       standard search path (cwd → `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gaussclaw/` → platform default)
  -v, --verbose...     Increase log verbosity. May be repeated (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -q, --quiet          Quiet mode: suppress non-error output
  -h, --help           Print help (see more with '--help')
  -V, --version        Print version
